description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Do you have a genuine passion for helping people to lose weight? An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and motivated band 5 dietitian to join our dynamic team within a Tier 3 Specialist Weight Management service, delivering high quality dietetic care to obese patients across the city. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will work with patients who have been assessed via a Tier 3 Multi-Disciplinary Team (MDT), and should ideally have experience of working within a weight management service, however full training and supervision will be provided. This is a rewarding and challenging post where you will have the opportunity to demonstrate excellent communication and behaviour change skills in both a 1-2-1 and group setting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A good understanding of the complex needs of obese individuals is desirable to support others to lose weight through empowerment and motivation. The post holder will have the opportunity to work alongside a range of specialists as part of an MDT, and be involved in assessing and discussing patients who are considering progressing onto a Tier 4 service to be considered for bariatric surgery. Applicants should be HCPC registered dietitians, with some post registration dietetic experience.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Excellent time management and organisational skills are essential, as the successful candidate will be expected to manage a busy caseload, ensuring all patients are adequately supported to help work towards their weight loss related goals. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role is a band 5 position, with the opportunity for progression to band 6. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please refer to the band 5 and band 6 job descriptions and the development role agreement attached to this advert. This role also offers the opportunity for Continuous CPD and additional training.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be based in the vibrant, cultural city of Hull which is continuing to thrive and grow after being awarded City of Culture in 2017.&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post will be based at &lt;strong&gt;Marfleet Health Centre, Hull but the&lt;strong&gt;successful&lt;/strong&gt; applicant will also be expected to work from various other bases across the city.&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Fulltime and part time hourswill be considered, however due to theneeds of the service part time hours would be a minimum of 30 hours per week.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
